%T A392756 687395
%N A392756 Number of equivalence classes of trees with n unlabeled nodes under the adjacency monomial E.
%C A392756 Here a tree T has an associated adjacency monomial E = x_1^(k_1) * x_2^(k_2) * x_3^(k_3) * ... with k_i being the number of pairs of vertices of T that are separated by i edges. Two trees are then considered equivalent if they have the same monomial E. The first occurrence of two trees being equivalent happens at n = 9.
%H A392756 John Tyler Rascoe, <a href="/A392756/a392756.py.txt">Python code</a>.
%e A392756 The tree below has E = x_1^4 * x_2^4 * x_3^2 so this is one equivalence class for a(5) = 3.
